  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nBlock proposing times are unstable causing missed proposed blocks\r\n\r\nPrater:\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-11-18 17-28-22](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/142455950-bd1bd4ed-431f-42a3-bf06-d0889aaaf1df.png)\r\n\r\nMainnet:\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-11-18 17-22-22](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/142455983-bd5de520-6956-4215-a05e-96d73a568362.png)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nPropose blocks strictly in under 3 seconds. Ideally in less than 1 second always\r\n\r\n**Todo**\r\n\r\nFirst we need to understand better what's slow about proposing a block\r\n- [ ] Add more histogram metrics on each step of proposing a block. See Lighthouse as a good example",
